Self-hosted, open source Braze/Iterable
text:
Hi all - we are building a self-hosted, open source Braze/Iterable type product - Plotline.

At our earlier roles, when we installed marketing automation tools, it bothered us how we needed to send our users’ data to 3rd parties. Exporting data from these tools cost us $manyK a month, and it felt wrong from a privacy perspective. We designed Plotline to solve these problems.

Plotline SDKs allow you to collect client and server events. You can also push events from your CDP of choice. The data is hosted on your cloud and you have API/SQL access.

1. You can segment users based on their behaviour and sync this data to ad platforms.

2. You can build communication journeys to send personalised email, push-notification, SMS, in-app banners.

We’re trying to work with a few early adopters before we launch on GitHub. Would anyone here be interested in trying it out?
